reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Variety and quality
reviews.reviewText: This is my first time scrapbooking, and this kit is great for beginners. It comes with a lot of different things, and all of them are pretty high quality. There's pages of designs, multiple sticker pages, sets of sheets (memo, to-do list), a small roll of decorative tape, and a notebook. I really liked the small, handheld notebook that it comes with because the texture of the paper and the multiple page bindings are great. The stickers adhere well for the most part, but there is no additional tape/double sided tape to attach the papers to the pages. Thankfully, they attach well with a separately purchased roll of double sided tape. Overall, the pack is very good and easy to use, as long as you have your own tape!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect Scrapbooking Kit!
reviews.reviewText: This Kit is a dream for anyone into bullet journaling or DIY journaling. The grid notebook is just the right size, and the flower-themed supplies add a beautiful touch. It's a fantastic birthday craft gift for myself and its high-quality materials and a great variety make this kit a must-have for all my projects. Love it! 🌸📔✨

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very pretty kit
reviews.reviewText: I really like Van Gogh, and this kit is beautiful. There is a good assortment of stickers, assorted size paper, washi tape, small envelopes, etc. I have used these in my journal, as well as photo albums and scrapbooks. The quality is good, and the colors are beautiful.

reviews.reviewText: This was A L O T smaller than I expected. The book is about palm size. But I ordered these for my daughters first scrapbook so it will be fine. But for an adult scrapbooker you might be disappointed. But cute cute.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Lovely for a present or a treat for oneself
reviews.reviewText: It's not as small as I thought it would be the reviews make it seem like it's microscopic but it's the size of my two hands combined plus a bit more so I think it does fairly nicely for 15$, not to mention the paper included feels like cardstock so very high quality, the van gogh/monet one is really nice and is the one I got, I would get it if you want to do scrapbooking or journaling or junk journaling or gifting it to someone who does those things

reviews.reviewText: This set of scrapbooking products is divine.
